77.4	Chiapas	Chiapas	Chiapas , officially Free and Sovereign State of Chiapas (Spanish: ), is one of the 31 states that, with the Federal District, comprise the 32 Federal Entities of Mexico. It is divided in 118 municipalities and its capital city is Tuxtla Gutierrez. Other important cites in Chiapas include San Cristóbal de las Casas, Comitán, and Tapachula. Located in Southwestern Mexico, it is the southernmost State of Mexico. It is bordered by the states of Tabasco to the north, Veracruz to the northwest and Oaxaca to the west. To the east Chiapas borders Guatemala, and to the south the Pacific Ocean.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1a/Flag_of_Chiapas.svg/160px-Flag_of_Chiapas.svg.png
